%e A126428 a(1) = 1, a(2) = 2; n = 3: k = 3, k-a(2) = 1 = a(2)-a(1), so a(3) > 3; k = 4: k-a(1) = 3 = a(1)+a(2), so a(3) > 4; k = 5: k-a(2) = 3 = a(1)+a(2), so a(3) > 5; k=6: k-a(1) = 5, k-a(2) = 4, k+a(1) = 7, k+a(2) = 8, a(2)-a(1) = 1, a(2)+a(1) = 3 are all distinct, hence a(3) = 6.
